VisualVM is a tool to monitor and troubleshoot Java applications.
It runs on Oracle/Sun JDK 6, but is able to monitor applications
running on JDK 1.4 and higher. It utilizes various available
technologies like jvmstat, JMX, the Serviceability Agent (SA), and
the Attach API to get the data and automatically uses the fastest
and most lightweight technology to impose minimal overhead on 
monitored applications.
